.SH "EXAMPLES"
.SS "Some typical use case for starting Guacharo from a console"
.sp
Starting Guacharo without any extra options, useful to any messages from guacharo in case something went not o.k.:
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
guacharo
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.sp
Starting Guacharo without any extensions or themes, useful if extensions may make some trouble:
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
guacharo \-safe-mode
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.sp
Starting Guacharo with a composing window:
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
guacharo \-compose
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.sp
Starting Guacharo with the default debugger:
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
/usr/lib/guacharo/run-mozilla.sh \-debug /usr/lib/guacharo/guacharo-bin
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.sp
Starting Guacharo with the specific debugger:
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
/usr/lib/guacharo/run-mozilla.sh \-\-debugger /foo/bar/debugger /usr/lib/guacharo/guacharo-bin
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}

